250 g Ground Turkey
1 unit(s) Lentils, canned
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
113 g Mirepoix
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
¼ cup Basil Pesto
7.5 g Chicken Stock Powder
1 g Chili Flakes
0.14 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
½ tbsp Oil*

Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.

Heat a large pot over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then turkey, peppers and mirepoix. Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with salt and pepper.

Add crushed tomatoes, stock powder, lentils including their liquid, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) chili flakes and 1/2 cup (1 cup) water. Bring up to a simmer.
Once simmering, cook for 4-5 min, stirring often, until stew thickens slightly. (TIP: Scrape up any brown bits from the bottom of the pan — this will add extra flavour!)

Divide stew between bowls.
Dollop pesto in a circular motion over top.
Sprinkle with feta and more chili flakes, to taste.

If you've opted to get turkey, when the pan is hot, add peppers along with mirepoix. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up turkey and stirring often until veggies have softened and turkey is cooked through.** Follow the rest of the recipe as written.